WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
A forest setting appears. A mother raccoon stands near a tree trunk.

00:04.000 --> 00:09.000
A small baby raccoon reaches toward the tree and looks up.

00:09.000 --> 00:14.000
The baby places its front paws on the bark and pauses.

00:14.000 --> 00:19.000
The mother raccoon stays close, facing the baby as if encouraging it.

00:19.000 --> 00:25.000
The baby climbs a little, then adjusts its grip and footing.

00:25.000 --> 00:31.000
The mother watches as the baby continues upward in short movements.

00:31.000 --> 00:36.000
The baby steadies itself and continues climbing near the tree.